---
const faqs = [
  {
    id: 1,
    question: "How do you measure digital impact?",
    answer:
      "We measure impact through a combination of technical performance metrics and the reduction of the 'Friction Tax' found in legacy public sites. Research indicates that leads from AI referrals convert at a 25X higher rate than traditional search, making citation frequency and sentiment in generative responses our primary KPIs.",
  },
  {
    id: 2,
    question: "What is the typical timeline for a V2V engagement?",
    answer:
      "A standard V2V (Visibility-to-Velocity) overhaul takes 8 to 12 weeks. This includes Prompt Mapping to identify stakeholder research queries and engineering fact-dense content to ensure your organization is cited as a primary authority by generative search engines.",
  },
  {
    id: 3,
    question: "Do you work with existing engineering teams?",
    answer:
      "Yes. We act as strategic architects, providing technical blueprints and institutional indexing leadership while collaborating with your internal teams for implementation. This partnership ensures that your content is not only visually optimized but also structured for 'Information Gain'—the unique data and expert insights that AI search engines prioritize when synthesizing answers.",
  },
  {
    id: 4,
    question: "Why focus on performance over aesthetics?",
    answer:
      "Speed and stability are the foundations of digital trust. AI models and generative engines value information presentation and fluency, often favoring fast-loading sites with clean architectures that allow for seamless data extraction. A slow site, regardless of beauty, creates friction in the 'parsing' process, making it less likely for AI to recommend your organization as a top resource.",
  },
  {
    id: 5,
    question:
      "How does GEO ensure our organization's mission-critical data is accurately cited by AI?",
    answer:
      "We implement 'Statistics Addition' and 'Quotation Addition' strategies, which have been shown to boost visibility in generative engine responses by up to 40%. By providing fact-dense content and authoritative data, we ensure your institutional knowledge acts as the grounding material AI uses to inform stakeholders.",
  },
  {
    id: 6,
    question:
      "Can AI search engines improve lead quality for donor engagement or regional investment?",
    answer:
      "Yes, AI search tools act as 'pre-qualifying agents,' providing potential partners with your credentials before they click through. Clicks from search results featuring AI-generated summaries are often of higher quality, with users spending more time on the site. Furthermore, AI-driven leads convert significantly better because trust is established within the AI’s authoritative response itself.",
  },
  {
    id: 7,
    question:
      "Does our legacy infrastructure hinder our visibility in tools like ChatGPT or Gemini?",
    answer:
      "Technical requirements for AI features largely mirror traditional SEO, but access is vital. Your infrastructure must explicitly allow specific crawlers like 'OAI-SearchBot' or 'PerplexityBot' in your robots.txt file to be eligible for citations. We ensure your architecture is not only crawlable but also optimized with schema markup (FAQ, Organization, Person) to clarify your identity for these engines.",
  },
  {
    id: 8,
    question: "Why is most institutional web data 'invisible' to AI?",
    answer:
      "Most public-private partnerships suffer from 'Information Bloat'—valuable data buried in non-responsive PDFs. This creates a 40% friction tax on discovery. We deploy the Revenue Engine Architect protocol to transform this fragmented data into machine-readable assets.",
  },
  {
    id: 9,
    question: "Does GEO improve lead quality for regional investment?",
    answer:
      "Yes. AI tools act as 'pre-qualifying agents,' providing potential partners with your credentials before they ever click through. Trust is established within the AI’s authoritative response itself, resulting in higher-intent leads for high-stakes projects.",
  },
  {
    id: 10,
    question: "What is 'Information Gain' and why does it matter for growth?",
    answer:
      "Information Gain is the unique, proprietary data your platform provide that competitors lack. Generative engines prioritize fresh perspective and fact-dense statistics to fill their knowledge gaps. Our framework ensures your exclusive data is the primary source cited for complex regional queries.",
  },
];
---

<script
  type="application/ld+json"
  set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    mainEntity: faqs.map((item) => ({
      "@type": "Question",
      name: item.question,
      acceptedAnswer: {
        "@type": "Answer",
        text: item.answer,
      },
    })),
  })}
/>

<section class="py-12 lg:py-24" id="faqs">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-6">
    <div class="text-center mb-12 lg:mb-16">
      <h2
        class="mb-4 text-2xl md:text-4xl tracking-tight font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white"
      >
        Institutional Intelligence <span class="text-brand-teal italic"
          >(FAQ)</span
        >
      </h2>
      <p
        class="text-lg md:text-xl tracking-tight font-medium text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 max-w-3xl mx-auto"
      >
        Mapping the technical transition from human-centric SEO to
        machine-readable authority.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div
      id="accordion-collapse"
      data-accordion="collapse"
      class="max-w-4xl mx-auto divide-y divide-slate-100 dark:divide-slate-800"
    >
      {
        faqs.map((item, index) => (
          <div class="py-2" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay={index * 200}>
            <h2 id={`accordion-collapse-heading-${index + 1}`}>
              <button
                type="button"
                class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-6 font-semibold rtl:text-right text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 hover:bg-slate-50 dark:hover:bg-slate-800/50 rounded-2xl transition-all duration-200 group gap-3"
                data-accordion-target={`#accordion-collapse-body-${index + 1}`}
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls={`accordion-collapse-body-${index + 1}`}
              >
                <span class="text-lg md:text-xl">{item.question}</span>
                <svg
                  data-accordion-icon
                  class="w-4 h-4 rotate-180 shrink-0 transition-transform duration-300 text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400"
                  aria-hidden="true"
                  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                  fill="none"
                  viewBox="0 0 10 6"
                >
                  <path
                    stroke="currentColor"
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    stroke-width="2"
                    d="M9 5 5 1 1 5"
                  />
                </svg>
              </button>
            </h2>
            <div
              id={`accordion-collapse-body-${index + 1}`}
              class="hidden"
              aria-labelledby={`accordion-collapse-heading-${index + 1}`}
            >
              <div class="p-6 pt-0">
                <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-lg leading-relaxed">
                  {item.answer}
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
